FIG. 1 is a schematic diagram of inlet and outlet pipelines of a multi-way valve system, wherein: 1. multi-way valve system;
2. feeding pipe for brine;
3. feeding pipe for low-magnesium solution for pushing back desorption solution;
4. feeding pipe for desorption solution;
5. discharging pipe for barren brine for pushing back desorption solution;
6. adsorption column;
7. discharging pipe for barren brine;
8. discharging pipe for lithium-containing brine;
9. discharging pipe for low-magnesium solution;
10. discharging pipe for qualified liquid;
11. feeding pipe for barren brine for pushing back desorption solution.

FIG. 2 is a schematic diagram of process flow of lithium extraction from salt lake brine, wherein:
12. tank for brine;
13. tank for desorption solution;
14. tank for barren brine;
15. tank for qualified liquid;
16. tank for low-magnesium solution;
N1, N2, N3, N4: adsorption towers.
